description.p:
Support for the claims and further embodiments are defined in the following itemized list:
1. A video display system having a video display device and a portable video display device, connected to each other for communication, wherein
the video display device comprises:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
other device video data producing means for producing other device video data in a data format different from a data format of the own device video data;
other device sound data producing means for producing other device sound data in a data format different from a data format of the own device sound data; and
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device, and the portable video display device comprises:
data receiving means for receiving the sent other device video data and the sent other device sound data; and
video and sound output means for displaying the received other device video data and reproducing the received other device sound data.
2. A video display system having a video display device and a portable video display device, connected to each other for communication, wherein
the video display device comprises:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
encoding means for encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data; and
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device, and the portable video display device comprises:
data receiving means for receiving the sent other device video data and the sent other device sound data; and
video and sound output means for decoding and displaying the received other device video data and decoding and reproducing the received other device sound data.
3. A video display device connected for communication to a portable video display device, comprising:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
encoding means for encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data; and
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device.
4. The video display device according to item 3, wherein the encoding means converts the own device video data into a size which the portable video display device is able to display, and then encodes the own device video data that has been converted in size, to thereby produce the other device video data.
5. The video display device according to item 3 or 4, wherein the encoding means reduces a number of channels of the own device sound data, and then encodes the own device sound data having a reduced number of channels, to thereby produce the other device sound data.
6. The video display device according to item 3, wherein
the own device video data producing means decodes encoded video data stored in storage means, to thereby produce the own device video data,
the own device sound data producing means decodes encoded sound data stored in the storage means, to thereby produce the own device sound data, and
the encoding means encodes at least one of the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format different from that of the encoded video data and the encoded sound data stored in the storage means.
7. The video display device according to item 3, wherein the encoding means encodes at least one of the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format selected based on information received from the portable video display device.
8. The video display device according to item 3, further comprising:
display mode switching means for receiving a connection start request and a connection end request sent from the portable video display device, then switching a display mode to an other device display mode in response to the received connection start request and to an own device display mode in response to the received connection end request;
wherein
the own device video data producing means outputs the produced own device video data to a predetermined frame buffer when the display mode is the own device display mode, and to a memory area different from the frame buffer when the display mode is the other device display mode,
the own device sound data producing means outputs the produced own device sound data to a predetermined sound buffer when the display mode is the own device display mode, and to a memory area different from the sound buffer when the display mode is the other device display mode,
the video and sound output means reads and displays the own device video data from the frame buffer, and reads and reproduces the own device sound data from the sound buffer, and
the encoding means reads and encodes the own device video data and the own device sound data from the memory areas.
9. The video display device according to item 3, wherein
the video display device is connected for communication to a plurality of portable video display devices, and further comprises information holding means for holding information correlating each of the portable video display devices to any of a plurality of groups,
the encoding means produces a plurality of same or different other device video data and a plurality of same or different other device sound data for the respective groups, and
the data sending means sends the other device video data and the other device sound data produced for the respective groups to the respective portable video display devices correlated to the respective groups according to the held information.
10. A control method for a video display device connected for communication to a portable video display device, comprising:
a step of producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
a step of producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
a step of displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
a step of encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data; and
a step of sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device.
11. A computer readable information storage medium storing a program for causing a video display device connected for communication to a portable video display device to function as:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data on video display means and reproducing the produced own device sound data on sound reproducing means;
encoding means for encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data; and
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device.

claim.claim-text:
A video display system having a video display device and a portable video display device, connected to each other for communication, wherein

the video display device comprises:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
other device video data producing means for producing other device video data in a data format different from a data format of the own device video data;
other device sound data producing means for producing other device sound data in a data format different from a data format of the own device sound data;
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device, and
a storing area that temporally stores the other device video data and the other device sound data,
wherein when content realized by the other device video data and the other device sound data is changed by an instruction of a user, the storing area is adjusted to have a size smaller than a size of the storing area when content is not changed, and
the portable video display device comprises:
data receiving means for receiving the sent other device video data and the sent other device sound data, which are stored in the storing area; and
video and sound output means for displaying the received other device video data and reproducing the received other device sound data, which are stored in the storing area.

A control method for a video display device connected for communication to a portable video display device, comprising:
a step of producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
a step of producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
a step of displaying the produced own device video data and reproducing the produced own device sound data;
a step of encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data;
a step of sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device; and
a step of storing temporally the other device video data and the other device sound data,
wherein when content realized by the other device video data and the other device sound data is changed by an instruction of a user, the storing area is adjusted to have a size smaller than a size of the storing area when content is not changed..

A computer readable information storage medium storing a program for causing a video display device connected for communication to a portable video display device to function as:
own device video data producing means for producing own device video data to be displayed on the video display device;
own device sound data producing means for producing own device sound data to be reproduced on the video display device;
video and sound output means for displaying the produced own device video data on video display means and reproducing the produced own device sound data on sound reproducing means;
encoding means for encoding the own device video data and the own device sound data into a data format which the portable video display device is able to handle, to thereby produce other device video data and other device sound data;
data sending means for sending the other device video data and the other device sound data to the portable video display device; and
storing means for temporally soring the other device video data and the other device sound data,
wherein when content realized by the other device video data and the other device sound data is changed by an instruction of a user, the storing area is adjusted to have a size smaller than a size of the storing area when content is not changed.
